MacKeeper is a utility software suite for macOS. The software distributor, Kromtech Alliance, states that MacKeeper secures, cleans, protects and optimizes a system. The product has received mixed reviews. It has been accused of not performing as advertised, being difficult to fully uninstall, and being heavily promoted though aggressive advertising and affiliate marketing. MacKeeper was alleged in a class-action lawsuit to have deceived users into paying for unneeded fixes, the lawsuit was settled in 2015 for US$2 million without any admission of guilt.
